oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Effect of Forage and TMR Particle Size on Cow Health and Milk Components
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Cramer, G.
Duffield, T.
Kelton, D.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: forage
mixed rations
particle size
health
production parameter
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Particle size of forages and total mixed rations plays an important role in the health and performance of dairy cattle. Objective of this study was to determine the effect of forage and total mixed ration (TMR) particle size on various health and production parameters in Ontario dairy herds.
